1
00:00:00,789 --> 00:00:06,350
It is so simple to jump into trading using
the RSI indicator without testing different

2
00:00:06,350 --> 00:00:11,491
settings, or educating yourself on the proper
interpretation of this indicator, because

3
00:00:11,491 --> 00:00:14,340
of a desire to grab money quickly!

4
00:00:14,340 --> 00:00:20,680
As a result, the RSI has become one of the
most widely misused indicators.

5
00:00:20,680 --> 00:00:25,540
Once understood and correctly applied, the
RSI has the ability to indicate whether prices

6
00:00:25,540 --> 00:00:31,000
are trending, when a market is overbought
or oversold, and the best price to enter or

7
00:00:31,000 --> 00:00:32,880
exit a trade.

8
00:00:32,880 --> 00:00:37,300
The relative strength index (RSI) it’s a
momentum oscillator that measures the speed

9
00:00:37,300 --> 00:00:39,360
and change of price movement.

10
00:00:39,360 --> 00:00:46,020
The RSI oscillates between 0 and 100 and it’s
often used to measure overbought and oversold

11
00:00:46,020 --> 00:00:52,400
conditions in the market, divergence or it
can be used to identify the general trend.

12
00:00:52,400 --> 00:00:58,720
Basically, the RSI is analyzing the total
number of down periods versus the total number

13
00:00:58,720 --> 00:01:02,680
of up periods and plots the average on the
RSI curve.

14
00:01:02,680 --> 00:01:07,540
There are many different techniques for using
it, but it can be altered depending on your

15
00:01:07,540 --> 00:01:09,620
specific needs.

16
00:01:09,620 --> 00:01:16,070
An overlooked method of using RSI is the use
of trend lines directly on the oscillator

17
00:01:16,070 --> 00:01:20,740
itself in much the same way that they are
used on price charts.

18
00:01:20,740 --> 00:01:25,420
Trend lines are one of the most common and
helpful tools in a trader's kit.

19
00:01:25,420 --> 00:01:31,420
They are used to show the price upwards, downwards,
and sometime sideways, movement.

20
00:01:31,420 --> 00:01:37,450
Confirmed trend lines are drawn by connecting
a cycle low, or high, with at least two other

21
00:01:37,450 --> 00:01:43,300
of the highest or lowest points on a chart,
to create a line of best fit.

22
00:01:43,300 --> 00:01:50,140
Connecting rising swing lows of the RSI in
an uptrend or lower swing highs in a downtrend,

23
00:01:50,140 --> 00:01:55,360
traders can find trading opportunities with
strong risk to reward setups.

24
00:01:55,360 --> 00:02:01,470
Because RSI measures the surge in closing
prices, when RSI changes direction and either

25
00:02:01,470 --> 00:02:07,320
breaks above or below a trend line, a significant
move in price can result.

26
00:02:07,320 --> 00:02:13,629
So, we’ll use the RSI indicator to show
us if the prevailing trend has ended and a

27
00:02:13,629 --> 00:02:14,819
new trend is underway.

28
00:02:14,819 --> 00:02:21,029
We’re not going to measure the overbought/oversold
conditions or as a crossover system, we’re

29
00:02:21,029 --> 00:02:25,329
going to take it one step further and look
for a break in momentum of the prevailing

30
00:02:25,329 --> 00:02:26,329
trend.

31
00:02:26,329 --> 00:02:31,069
What I mean by this is that we’re going
to look at the changes in prices relative

32
00:02:31,069 --> 00:02:35,859
to the changes in the peak and the valley
that the RSI indicator will generate.

33
00:02:35,859 --> 00:02:41,379
Trend lines placed on this oscillator provide
an additional level of precision as well as

34
00:02:41,379 --> 00:02:43,560
additional trade setups.

35
00:02:43,560 --> 00:02:49,129
Because the signals are leading rather than
lagging, stops can be placed relatively close

36
00:02:49,129 --> 00:02:50,749
to the entry point.

37
00:02:50,749 --> 00:02:54,249
This allows for a good risk to reward trading
opportunity.

38
00:02:54,249 --> 00:03:01,819
The RSI-trend line approach works best on
higher timeframes but it can be used on any

39
00:03:01,819 --> 00:03:04,299
time frame, for day trading for example.

40
00:03:04,299 --> 00:03:10,370
The rules of this technique are straightforward,
we only need to connect the most recent RSI

41
00:03:10,370 --> 00:03:15,659
peaks or valleys with a trend line and we
search for a breakout of the trend line, which

42
00:03:15,659 --> 00:03:22,450
will warn us that the market has lost its
steam and the prevailing trend has lost its

43
00:03:22,450 --> 00:03:23,760
momentum.

44
00:03:23,760 --> 00:03:29,190
There is one more condition that needs to
be satisfied in order to enter a trade, we

45
00:03:29,190 --> 00:03:34,959
need for the price to still be trading below
its trend line, so we’ll need the RSI trend

46
00:03:34,959 --> 00:03:39,680
line to be broken, and the price to be trading
below its trend line.

47
00:03:39,680 --> 00:03:45,669
This is the most important principle in order
for the RSI-trend line strategy to work because

48
00:03:45,669 --> 00:03:51,750
it tells us there is also a divergence between
momentum and price.

49
00:03:51,750 --> 00:03:57,510
Momentum always goes ahead of price and that’s
the reason why this strategy can yield a great

50
00:03:57,510 --> 00:03:58,790
return.

51
00:03:58,790 --> 00:04:04,089
The breaking of an RSI trend line usually
precedes the break of a trend line on the

52
00:04:04,089 --> 00:04:08,299
price chart, providing an advance warning
of a reversal.

53
00:04:08,299 --> 00:04:13,310
Therefore, recognizing the break of the RSI
trend line can be an important and profitable

54
00:04:13,310 --> 00:04:17,080
indicator that the price direction is about
to change.

55
00:04:17,080 --> 00:04:19,390
This is a leading signal.

56
00:04:19,390 --> 00:04:24,920
a leading signal appears before the new trend
or reversal occurs.

57
00:04:24,920 --> 00:04:28,610
RSI, in its nature, is a lagging indicator.

58
00:04:28,610 --> 00:04:34,880
Lagging indicators only give signals after
the price change is clearly forming a trend.

59
00:04:34,880 --> 00:04:39,380
The downside is that you’d be a little late
in entering a position.

60
00:04:39,380 --> 00:04:45,310
Often the biggest gains of a trend occur in
the first few bars, so by using a lagging

61
00:04:45,310 --> 00:04:50,080
indicator you could potentially miss out on
much of the profit.

62
00:04:50,080 --> 00:04:55,760
That’s, when trading the RSI trend line
breakout, you’ll get leading signals.

63
00:04:55,760 --> 00:05:00,780
Now you’re probably saying to yourself,
“Oh, I’m going to get rich with leading

64
00:05:00,780 --> 00:05:01,780
indicators!”

65
00:05:01,780 --> 00:05:05,300
Since you would be able to profit from a new
trend right at the start.

66
00:05:05,300 --> 00:05:06,380
You’re right.

67
00:05:06,380 --> 00:05:11,150
You would “catch” the entire trend every
single time if the leading indicator was correct

68
00:05:11,150 --> 00:05:12,220
every single time.

69
00:05:12,220 --> 00:05:14,270
But it won’t be.

70
00:05:14,270 --> 00:05:18,330
When you use leading indicators, you will
experience a lot of fakeouts.

71
00:05:18,330 --> 00:05:22,910
That’s why it’s important to look closely
at the price action.

72
00:05:22,910 --> 00:05:28,120
If you would take a trade every time you spot
a RSI trend line breakout, you would soon

73
00:05:28,120 --> 00:05:31,070
find out that the outcome is not as expected.

74
00:05:31,070 --> 00:05:37,450
The RSI trend line has leading qualities,
but after all it’s still an indicator.

75
00:05:37,450 --> 00:05:38,900
You need to analyze the price.

76
00:05:38,900 --> 00:05:45,270
You need to draw key support and resistance
levels, to identify the trend and take RSI

77
00:05:45,270 --> 00:05:50,160
trend lines in the direction of the main trend.

78
00:05:50,160 --> 00:05:52,140
Here is a common mistake.

79
00:05:52,140 --> 00:05:58,150
Many traders that implement the RSI trend
line breakout approach, use it as a reversal

80
00:05:58,150 --> 00:05:59,240
signal.

81
00:05:59,240 --> 00:06:05,120
They see an upward trend, they spot a RSI
trend line breakout and go short.

82
00:06:05,120 --> 00:06:09,750
This could work, yes, but it’s not the most
consistent way of using it.

83
00:06:09,750 --> 00:06:13,240
I use it in a more conservative way.

84
00:06:13,240 --> 00:06:19,270
When I spot the same uptrend, i search for
RSI trend line signals that offer buy opportunities.

85
00:06:19,270 --> 00:06:24,230
I have zero interest in RSI signals indicating
short trades.

86
00:06:24,230 --> 00:06:26,660
I go with the main trend.

87
00:06:26,660 --> 00:06:32,900
In GBPUSD chart, we noticed some RSI trend
line breaks.

88
00:06:32,900 --> 00:06:38,640
The use of the trend line provided additional
visual confirmation that a trade opportunity

89
00:06:38,640 --> 00:06:40,150
is near.

90
00:06:40,150 --> 00:06:47,830
The use of trend line breaks gave buy signals
a few candles before the actual move.

91
00:06:47,830 --> 00:06:54,030
In this another chart, we can have a representation
of how a short setup would look like.

92
00:06:54,030 --> 00:07:00,610
We have the price making lower lows and lower
high, so we are definitely in a downtrend.

93
00:07:00,610 --> 00:07:04,330
We added the main support and resistance levels.

94
00:07:04,330 --> 00:07:08,250
Then we identified the RSI trend line breakouts.

95
00:07:08,250 --> 00:07:14,420
In terms of stop loss level, a common practice
is to use the candle on which the RSI broke

96
00:07:14,420 --> 00:07:21,760
its trend line, so in the case of our short
setup our SL would be above that candle.

97
00:07:21,760 --> 00:07:25,630
In real time trading, this isn’t best practice.

98
00:07:25,630 --> 00:07:29,270
That’s why I rely on recent market swings.

99
00:07:29,270 --> 00:07:33,970
I aim to place my stop loss above an important
swing.

100
00:07:33,970 --> 00:07:39,320
If you prefer a better visualization of the
trend, add a long term moving average, and

101
00:07:39,320 --> 00:07:43,020
take trades in its main direction.

102
00:07:43,020 --> 00:08:05,530
Here are other examples of RSI trend line
trades.

103
00:08:05,530 --> 00:08:09,340
Regarding the settings, or better said, the
period of RSI.

104
00:08:09,340 --> 00:08:15,430
RSI like many other oscillators is defaulted
to a 14 period setting.

105
00:08:15,430 --> 00:08:21,200
This means the indicator looks back 14 bars
on whatever graph you may be viewing, to create

106
00:08:21,200 --> 00:08:22,680
its reading.

107
00:08:22,680 --> 00:08:27,020
Even though 14 is the default period, that
may not make it the best setting for your

108
00:08:27,020 --> 00:08:28,080
trading.

109
00:08:28,080 --> 00:08:34,789
Normally short-term traders use a smaller
period, such as a nine period RSI, to replicate

110
00:08:34,789 --> 00:08:37,829
shorter term movements in the market.

111
00:08:37,829 --> 00:08:44,509
Longer-term traders may opt for a higher period,
such as a 21 period RSI or even 50.

112
00:08:44,509 --> 00:08:49,790
Depending on your trading style, you can lower
your RSI to increase sensitivity or you could

113
00:08:49,790 --> 00:08:53,110
raise it to decrease sensitivity.

114
00:08:53,110 --> 00:08:59,019
Keep in mind that on lower timeframes, with
lower RSI settings, you will get a lot of

115
00:08:59,019 --> 00:09:03,130
false signals, because the indicator will
have increased sensitivity.

116
00:09:03,130 --> 00:09:09,769
So, maybe it’s better to increase the value
of the RSI if you want to back test this technique

117
00:09:09,769 --> 00:09:12,199
on smaller timeframes.

118
00:09:12,199 --> 00:09:17,449
If you want a smoother analysis, with less
noise, go on higher timeframes.

119
00:09:17,449 --> 00:09:23,910
Here you could use a lower period on the RSI,
which will offer more trend line opportunities,

120
00:09:23,910 --> 00:09:29,990
but you could also adopt a less sensitive
approach, by using a higher period RSI, like

121
00:09:29,990 --> 00:09:32,259
the 21 for example.

122
00:09:32,259 --> 00:09:38,240
The key is to back test and find the best
approach that works with your trading style.

123
00:09:38,240 --> 00:09:45,749
The RSI is a powerful tool that can offer
a great assistance on when to buy and when

124
00:09:45,749 --> 00:09:47,439
to sell.

125
00:09:47,439 --> 00:09:52,790
Sometimes it can also predict the trend other
indicators are too slow to acknowledge.

126
00:09:52,790 --> 00:09:57,370
An important tip is that you shouldn’t chase
the trades, let them come to you.

127
00:09:57,370 --> 00:10:01,100
RSI is an indicator and just follow the price.

128
00:10:01,100 --> 00:10:05,740
You should be patient and wait for a clear
break of its trend line.

129
00:10:05,740 --> 00:10:11,889
Maybe sometimes, you should wait to see how
the first candle acts after the breakout and

130
00:10:11,889 --> 00:10:13,980
after that take your trade.

131
00:10:13,980 --> 00:10:19,560
If you got any value from this and learned
something new, leave us a like to show your

132
00:10:19,560 --> 00:10:20,560
support.

133
00:10:20,560 --> 00:10:24,950
Also don’t forget to subscribe and click
the bell icon to stay in touch with new uploads.

134
